  (1, 'What happens to memories during sleep?', 'They are erased', 'They are consolidated', 'They are transferred', 'They are created', 'B'),
  (2, 'How many hours of sleep do adults need per night?', '5-6 hours', '6-7 hours', '7-9 hours', '9-11 hours', 'C'),
  (3, 'Which is NOT mentioned as a risk of chronic sleep deprivation?', 'Obesity', 'Heart disease', 'Blindness', 'Depression', 'C'),
  (4, 'How does poor sleep affect decision-making?', 'It has no effect', 'It improves it', 'It impairs it', 'It speeds it up', 'C'),
  (5, 'What is one recommended strategy for improving sleep?', 'Exercise right before bed', 'Avoid screens before bed', 'Drink coffee in the evening', 'Sleep at different times each night', 'B')
